<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">If you want to get in it to make some minor things for yourself and your friends (like +2 and +3 rings, earrings, and bracelets) sure..go do it.. If you think you want to make plat. jewlery and make big money..I would rethink it.  It costs alot to learn the trade.  I am at lvl 180 and still fail at Plat. pieces.  Thats 100+ pp per try.  <br>
And just to continue training to lvl 200 costs me 12pp each failure which is 2 out of 10 trys.  In short..if u really want to do it..get a jewelers kit..put 3-4 traning points into it.. by lvl 50 u will know if you wish to continue..  good luck<hr>Crystalmoon, Enchantress<br>
Master Jeweler, Mith Marr<br>
Diamonds are a girls best friend</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
