<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Unless you are an enchanter, or have a good friend who's one and is always in the same zone as you, forget it. To get your skill to 200, you acn blow 1000pp or more...that's a lot of money. If you are an enchanter, and can get money, then go for it. If you aren't, try tailoring. It's in demand a lot, easy to do, and a lot cheaper then most of the other trade skills. But before you do any skill, put as many points into it as you can...It's a lot easier to start, and you can begin to make more advanced stuff. Also, I wouldn't recommend getting into any trade skills until 20, with the exception of baking(sucks, and nobody really needs it) or tailoring.<p>

Well, my 2cp<p>

Suinadie Gogglefizzer<br>
Gnomish Necromancer of the 22nd level<br>
