im lvl 40 now and my jewel skill is at 193 now. to come to this point i invested 5 or 6kpp<br>
, not counted the resell of the "training jewels"(not enchanted metall with jewel), which will make it to closly 8 or 10kpp to reach this 193 skill pts.<br>
i played my ench for 4 month and started jewelskill with my first few pp i earned( around lvl 5 or 6) invested 21 skill pts from lvling to get a cheap beginning ;)<br>
to come to the point what i have to say now this skill becomes real fun. just to tell u a little story :<br>
 a guy hailed some day in FV on kunark my if i could make some jewels for him in gold and plat. "sure" i said "but plat is not trivial and my skill is  not at 200"(btw PLAT WILL BE NEVER TRIVIAL-maby with the new patch). i told him my suggested prices for the items he wanted and how many trys i sure will have to do to make em, around 2kpp for all items on the first successful try, and he agreed ,gave me 5kpp and said i shall make the items and keep the rest :)).<br>
ok , i  made the gold items first -no fails, the plat items i failed 5 to 7 times but made all ordered items he wished. at the end 1kpp left for my services :)). i told him whats left and he said its ok just keep it and the he gave me a YAKEESHA SHORT SWORD as a tip, i didnt believed what i saw in the trade window but it was one.<br>
for sure this will not happen with every customer but it shows u ONE DAY THIS SKILL IS WORTH THE SWEET AND PAIN U INVESTED.<br>
u can trust me ,more then one time i wished this skill to hell or elswhere but now im satisfied with it after this story happend.<br>
but i have to mention u SHOULD be a enchanter to earn some real money with this skill ;)<p>

hope this answers your question<hr>Valkyree Soulfire <br>
