<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">You asked about pricing.  My general rule is silver/electrum, shoot for 50% profit.  That is, if it cost 10pp to make charge 15pp to sell.  These metals fail rarely if done correctly and you will stay ahead in the win/loss column.  However, when you start selling gold jewlry try a 100% mark up, this seems to work.  <br>
That said I do refine my pricing.  I find I sell specific items to specific classes and I can get away with adjusting my price structure.  Let me explain.  I make Gold Black Pearl Chokers (+7 DEX/AGI).  There are alot of monks on Kunark that just love this thing.  I buy the pearls for 30pp from players (21pp from vendors when I can find) and pay 10pp per gold bar.  Total cost is 40pp.  When I started selling this Item for 80pp I got 5 tells to start to buy.  The next night I changed my price to 100pp, still sold 4 a night easy, I am now selling these chokers for 120pp in Lake of Ill Omen and Frontier Mountains (Luclin).  <p>

I like playing for exp and selling my Jewls for pp.  Done right you can travel and carry the correct jewls and metals on you at all times and make/sell what is in demand.  That way, you maximize your profits once you know what classes are around and what they are going to need(STR items in Permafrost).<p>

Good Luck<hr>Siorn Racharm<br>
Luclin</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
